  "texts": [
    "**Avoid using placeholders**: Do not use vague input values with placeholders.",
    "Instead, first obtain the actual values for the placeholders (using other tools if necessary) and then use them in the input.",
    "-Incorrect (with placeholders): {{\"id\": `<id>`, \"account_number\": <account_number>}} -Incorrect (with placeholders and comments): {{\"id\": `<id>`, \"account_number\": < account_number>}} Note: The user needs to fill in the `<id>`and <account_number> -Correct (with actual sourced values): {{\"id\": \"a4bjb5nw1m\",\"account_number\":",
    "\"9012-0678-236\"}}",
    "Here is an example for how to format your response."
  ]
